childElements.name: ExamInstructionsNote
childElements.propertySetConfig:
{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock3", "text" : "

ARIZONA SUPREME COURT

Registration for Examination

  • Registration: Pre-registration is required. Space will be reserved on a first come, first served basis. A space is not reserved until you complete payment of the exam fee. Current exam fees can be found in the Arizona Code of Judicial Administration. 

  • Examination: On your scheduled exam day, please arrive at least 15 minutes prior to the start time to register for the exam. Registration will begin one half hour prior to the exam start time.

  • Exam Retries A re-registration fee will apply for any applicant who registers for an examination date and fails to appear at the designated site on the scheduled date and time. 

  • Accomodation Reasonable accommodation will be provided to a qualified applicant with a disability in accordance with the Americans with Disabilities Act. If you have a disability and require an accommodation, contact the Certification and Licensing Division at (602) 452-3378 at least two weeks prior to the examination date for additional information regarding the documentation to be submitted.
WE DO NOT ACCEPT CASH PAYMENTS AND ALL FEES ARE NON-REFUNDABLE.
By selecting "Schedule Exam", you agree to the terms outlined on this page.

Additional Information

You will be required to present two forms of personal identification (at least one form must be a government-issued picture I.D.; one indicating your date of birth). Subsequent to your participation in the exam, you will receive notice of your results via U.S. Mail. Please do not contact the Certification and Licensing Division for exam result information. Exam results are released by mail to the examinee only. If you are unsuccessful in your attempt to complete the examination requirement, the notice forwarded to you will provide instructions for registering to retake the exam.

 
", "show" : null, "dataJSON" : false, "HTMLTemplateId" : "", "textKey" : "", "sanitize" : false }
